description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking to recruit to our intermediate tier rota to replace our current cohort who are predicted to successfully gain formal training posts in Emergency Medicine.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This job is designed for UK trained or IMG candidates wishing to pursue a career in Emergency Medicine but not yet ready to apply for training or to work at Middle Grade level.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advantages of this post over standard ED Junior Doctor posts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.       &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reduced out of areas clinical component to facilitate learning &amp; development.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2.       &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8 Hours timetabled CPD every 2 weeks for self &amp; portfolio development in addition to standard study leave.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3.       &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Access to junior &amp; senior in house teaching programs for 4 hours a week including advanced Simulation training.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4.       &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven track record of previous post holders successfully gaining entry into UK Emergency Training for UK trained &amp; IMG background.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5.       &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supervision &amp; mentorship from Consultant body qualified as RCEM examiners, ARCP panelists &amp; National run through training interviewers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
